I would highlight in the docs of `_inherit_docstrings` that it may overwrite docstrings of the base classes of the decorated object. It's obvious when looking into the code, but not obvious at all when you're reading the function's contract.

```python
from modin.utils import _inherit_docstrings

class DocsContainer:
    def method():
        """Doc-string."""
        pass

class Base:
    def method(): # Not documented method
        pass

@_inherit_docstrings(DocsContainer)
class Derived(Base):
    pass

print(Derived.method.__doc__) # Doc-string.
print(Base.method.__doc__)    # Doc-string.

```

